\par \pard \ql \li0\ri0 \sb120 \fi360 QUESTION PRESENTED
\par \pard \ql \li0\ri0 \sb120 \fi360 Whether a school district with a history of de jure segregation may unilaterally abandon a court-ordered desegregation plan for elementary school students while residential segregation caused in part by past unlawful state action ensures that inner-city neighborhood schools would be virtually all-black.  \b \i0 \ul0 [*2]\b0 \i0 \ul0  
\par \pard 
\par \pard 
\par \b \i0 \ul0 \pard \ql \li0\ri0 \sb0 \fi0 INTERESTS:\b0 \i0 \ul0  The American Jewish Committee, founded in 1906, seeks to protect the security and constitutional rights of Jews in America through the preservation of the rights of all Americans.  We have been concerned with the inequities of segregated schooling since the late 1940's, when we sponsored research on the effects of de jure segregation.  This research was later cited by the U.S. Supreme Court in Brown v. Board of Education, 347 U.S. 483, 494 n.11 (1954). AJC was amicus curiae in both Brown and Keyes v. School District No. 1, 413 U.S. 189 (1973), and we view the instant case as critical to the preservation of the principles established in those cases.
\par \pard \ql \li0\ri0 \sb0 \fi0 STATEMENT OF INTEREST
\par \pard \ql \li0\ri0 \sb120 \fi360 The Asian American Legal Defense and Education Fund is a national civil rights organization that addresses the critical problems facing Asian Americans.  Our civil rights priorities include anti-Asian Violence, Immigrant Rights, Voting Rights, Labor and Employment Rights, and Redress for Japanese Americans incarcerated in camps during World War II.  The Oklahoma City school system has yet to uproot the vestiges of de jure segregation and achieve a unitary school system.  Continuing desegregation efforts in education must be maintained to achieve equal opportunity in education for minority Americans who, like African Americans, were compelled to attend segregated schools.  Gong Lum v. Rice, 275 U.S. 78 (1927).
\par \pard \ql \li0\ri0 \sb120 \fi360 The National Council of La Raza is a non-profit, tax-exempt corporation dedicated to improving life opportunities for the more than 20 million Hispanics in the United States.  NCLR represents over 120 affiliates, which are community-based organizations serving the Hispanic community in 32 states and the District of Columbia.  As a long time advocate of Hispanics' rights to equal educational opportunities, we oppose the weakening of the hard-won remedial procedures currently in place which work to resolve long-standing educational discrimination.
\par \pard \ql \li0\ri0 \sb120 \fi360 The Puerto Rican Legal Defense and Education Fund, Inc. (PRLDEF) is a national civil rights organization representing Puerto Rican and other Latinos.  PRLDEF is and has been counsel to the Latino community in a number of school desegregation cases in the Northeast.  The issue presented in this case is vital to the continued success of several ongoing desegregation efforts and the provision of quality education.
\par \pard \ql \li0\ri0 \sb120 \fi360 The Unitarian Universalist Association is a religious organization consisting of over 1000 member churches and 100,000 members located throughout the country.  It intervenes in cases where racial justice concerns and principles are importantly at issue.
\par \pard \ql \li0\ri0 \sb120 \fi360 The YWCA of the U.S.A. is a national membership organization whose mission is the elimination of racism and the empowerment of women.  As adopted by its national convention, the YWCA supports "measures to assure the full compliance of vigorous enforcement of laws requiring desegregation of the public schools."
\par \pard 
